        "title": "Time Series Supply Chain Dataset",
        "subtitle": "Orders, Pieces, and Revenue for Daily Deliveries in Different Locations",
        "description": "This dataset contains 5 years of simulated delivery data for several customers in several different locations. The purpose of this dataset is to mimic real-world delivery patters by including seasonality, demand spikes, and holiday closures. This dataset is perfect for anyone trying to practice time-series forecasting, demand planning, or supply chain analysis.\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\n5 years of synthetic delivery data for several customers and locations\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nWorkDate: Date of delivery\nCustomer: Customer serviced\nLocation: Hub location where orders originated from\nBusinessType: Type of delivery done\nOrderCount: Number of orders\nNumberOfPieces: Number of pieces\nTotalRevenue: Total revenue collected from deliveries\n",
